The Nigerian workers have been urged to brace up for 2020 challenges and justify government efforts on them. The Vicar in charge of Baptist Church Okeagbe Akoko North West Local Government Area of Ondo State, Rev. David Balogun made the admonition during the annual inter religious New Year prayers jointly held by workers of Anwl in collaboration with local government chapter of Nigeria Inter Religious Council (NIREC) at Okeagbe Akoko the council headquarters. He said they should always appreciate and reciprocate God’s grace and protection over their families for making possible for to cross over to another year in good health and sound minds. “Nigerian workers should brace up for the challenges ahead on the year 2020 and appreciates government efforts on them”, he said. Also  speaking, the Secretary NIREC in the local government and the Chief Imam Taqumideen Society of Nigeria, Sheik Hussein Mohahamed  urged workers to imbibe the spirit of fairness, justice and equity as preached by Prophet Muhammad and this made life worthy of living while here on earth and in the hereafter which would be their final rest abode. The Muslim cleric warned workers against back biting, acrimony and insolence saying all these were attributes of devil which might not allow things to work. The chairman of Nirec in the council area, Alhaji Ibrahim kilani noted that God answered the council prayers last year as there was no negative development. He praised the chairman, local government caretaker committee, Elder Ayodele Akande and his management for changing the image of the council to a better one. Kilani called for concerted efforts to move the council forward. 